---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Vital Sign — Heart Rate View
description: number display of heart rate in beats per minute (BPM)
---

{% from "components/vital-sign-heart-rate-as-beats-per-minute-view/macro.njk" import vitalSignHeartRateAsBeatsPerMinuteView %}

<h2>Default</h2>
<p>{{ vitalSignHeartRateAsBeatsPerMinuteView({
  value: 72,
  label: "Heart rate"
}) }}</p>

<h2>Out-of-range values</h2>
<p>The view is visual only; styling a value as abnormal is the
  consumer's choice. Here we apply a
  <code>classes: "abnormal"</code> modifier:</p>

<p>{{ vitalSignHeartRateAsBeatsPerMinuteView({
  value: 118,
  label: "Heart rate (tachycardia)",
  classes: "abnormal"
}) }}</p>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>The unit is wrapped in
  <code>&lt;abbr title="beats per minute"&gt;bpm&lt;/abbr&gt;</code>
  so screen readers can expand "bpm" into its full form.</p>
